A man who attempted to take his own life by jumping into the lagoon has been rescued. A man who wanted to end his own life by jumping into the lagoon at the Lekki-Ikoyi Bridge has been rescued. In a video shared online, the suicidal man is seen sitting on the floor, looking dejected, as his rescuers flanked him and held onto both arms to prevent him from going over the bridge into the lagoon below: Click the link below to Watch video: Man rescued from committing suicide by jumping into the lagoon in Lekki Credit: @olayinkayankee A post shared by  Lindaikejiblog (@lindaikejiblogofficial) on May 9, 2019 at 6:13am PDT Source